@edgars.flavors 
Finally reopening after a long closing

One of the finest Agave Oriented bar in Europe can be find in Brussels, Owned and run by @tania.shamshur  who running incredible agave spirit program specializing in independent spirits. Boutique spirits, creative cocktails and great atmosphere a must visit while in Brussels.

Dama Rita 

6cl @ladamatequila 
2cl @cointreau 
3cl lime juice
1cl Tonka bean syrup

Pairing with @ladamatequila and some chocolate and jam by La Dama’s Global brand Ambassador Tania 

Jalisco Negroni 

3cl @ladamatequila 
2,5cl of walnut infused Campari 
2,5cl of Sweet Vermouth 

Paired with chocolate by @jerome_grimonpon_chocolatier  Colombian (Narino) 77% cacao (fruity acidity,slight bitterness, notes of banana and tobacco ) 

Breakfast in Los Altos 

6cl of La Dama Tequila 
2cl of @drink_xila 
2cl of lemon juice 
1 spoon of a bit of Jam made with La Dama 
2 dashes or Verbena bitters

Paired with chocolate with Mexican cocoa 70% of cacao ( red fruits, smoked cacao ) from Chontalpa , using native cacao’s “criollo”.

Brasserie Zédel / London / UK

Brasserie Zedel is a grand Parisian brasserie with an authentic Art Deco interior. Hidden away behind the
ZL Café in the heart of Piccadilly, it serves traditional French food at exceptional value and has a Bib Gourmand to its name.

@brasseriezedel 
The building also plays host to a classic American bar, Bar Américain and a live music and cabaret venue,
The Crazy Coqs. Open daily from early until late.
